  "prompt": "Why did Thor's hammer shake in the movie \u2018Avengers: Age of Ultron\u2019 when Captain America tried to lift it?",
  "response": "In \"Avengers: Age of Ultron,\" Thor's hammer (Mjolnir) slightly moved when Captain America tried to lift it, which suggests that Steve Rogers was potentially worthy of wielding the hammer. While Cap couldn't fully lift it, the subtle movement implied that he was almost capable of doing so, which surprised Thor. This scene hinted that Captain America might have some inherent worthiness, though not quite enough to completely lift Mjolnir at that point. The moment became a subtle but significant character moment in the film, suggesting Cap's great moral character.\n\nLater films, specifically \"Avengers: Endgame,\" would confirm that Captain America was indeed worthy and could fully wield Thor's hammer in battle.",
